title: Vigo County Jail Log: June 2, 2018
content: The following individuals were booked into the Vigo County Jail by area law enforcement Friday and Saturday, based on jail records. Charges are recommended by arresting officers but are not final until the Vigo County prosecutor reviews the case and files official charges.    Friday    • Danielle K. Baugh, 27, 2400 block of Dillman Street, Terre Haute. Booked 9:46 a.m. Domestic battery.    • Harry D. Brenton, 41, 3300 block of East Park Avenue, Terre Haute. Booked 11:48 a.m. Operating a motor vehicle without ever receiving a license (two counts).    • Brandon L. Harris, 32, 100 block of East Miller Avenue, West Terre Haute. Booked 12:01 p.m. False informing, possession of methamphetamine and possession of paraphernalia.    • Austin R. Wilson, 34, 800 block of North 13th 1/2 Street, Terre Haute. Booked 2:41 p.m. Intimidation, residential entry, strangulation and battery resulting in bodily injury.    • Jacob M. Hanna, 24, 400 block of South 15th Street, Terre Haute. Booked 4:24 p.m. Possession of a synthetic drug or synthetic drug lookalike substance, possession of methamphetamine and possession of paraphernalia.    • Neil S. Eisman, 23, 11200 block of East Gibbs Avenue, Rosedale. Booked 5:44 p.m. Invasion of privacy.    • John R. Lattin, 25, 1600 block of North Stop 18 Street, Terre Haute. Booked 6:12 p.m. Operating a motor vehicle without ever receiving a license, driving while suspended and disregarding an official traffic control device.    • Jared M. Menestrina, 35, 30 block of Monroe Boulevard, Terre Haute. Booked 8:32 p.m. Unlawful possession of a syringe, maintaining a common nuisance and possession of paraphernalia.    • Jonathan M. Hall, 26, 1500 block of South 18th Street, Terre Haute. Booked 9:57 p.m. Escape from lawful detention and dealing in methamphetamine.    Saturday         • Tommie H. Lee, 40, 2100 block of South Center Street, Terre Haute. Booked 12:22 a.m. Invasion of privacy.    • Meloney K. Collins, 20, 2900 block of Ijams Drive, Terre Haute. Booked 1:24 a.m. Out-of-town warrant.     • Quinn Martin, 21, 5900 block of Sycamore Forge Drive, Indianapolis. Booked 3:28 a.m. Carrying a handgun without a license and possession of marijuana.    • Jeffrey Whitsit, 25, 1500 block of Woodley Avenue, Terre Haute. Booked 4:09 a.m. Battery and intimidation.    • Logan M. Galloway, 19, 400 block of Linwood Drive, Greencastle. Booked 5:43 a.m. Operating a vehicle while intoxicated, possession of a synthetic drug or synthetic drug lookalike substance and possession of paraphernalia.    Under the law, criminal charges are merely accusations, and the defendant is presumed innocent unless and until proven guilty.
